Adalgisa (second from left in the picture), is 28 years old and a mother of three school-aged children. Her husband is a fisherman. With the wages from her part-time job, Adalgisa and her husband can barely make ends meet. In order to have an additional source of income, Adalgisa is looking forward to setting up a small business. She’s requested a loan of $725 to buy women’s clothing to retail in her neighborhood. The entrepreneur says that it’s really hard to sustain the kids, but she hopes that her venture will help her to improve her family’s living conditions. 

Adalgisa will receive her loan together with these following women:
Claribel H., who sells jewelry;
Claribel B., who sells clothing;
Rosa Iris C., who sells women’s clothing;
Ana Karen P., who owns a cafeteria
